Project Overview

The project involves two controllers: STM32CX and STM32FX. The system is designed to control multiple relay banks and verify their operation through data communication between the two controllers.

STM32CX Controller Operation

The STM32CX controller manages 4 banks, and each bank contains:

4 relays

2 digital outputs

1 input pin (IN)

1 output pin (OUT)

The STM32CX operates continuously or can run each bank sequentially with a defined delay.

During operation, a gray code corresponding to the active bank is sent from STM32CX to STM32FX.

The IN pin of STM32CX is connected to STM32FX. When STM32FX drives this pin low, STM32CX changes the bank operating speed to 8 ms.

STM32CX also transfers the running bank data to STM32FX for verification and monitoring.

STM32FX Controller Operation

The STM32FX controller declares the bank data and reads digital inputs from the STM32CX.

It compares the received data with the expected bank data:

If both match → displays PASS

If they differ → displays FAIL

STM32FX sends a low signal on the IN pin to STM32CX whenever the user triggers an input command.

Function Summary

This project effectively controls and monitors multiple relay banks using two STM32 microcontrollers.

STM32CX handles relay control and bank operation.

STM32FX performs data verification and feedback control, ensuring reliable synchronization between both controllers.
